threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a malicious IoT botnet agent, specifically a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt malware families. The binary contains a massive embedded dictionary of default credentials used for automated telnet brute-forcing (seen in sub_4114d8, e.g., 'root:Pon521', 'admin:Xpon@Olt9417#'). It exhibits typical bot behaviors: clearing system firewall rules with 'iptables -F', scanning the '/proc' directory to identify and terminate competing processes, and utilizing multiple download methods (busybox wget, tftp, ftpget, and curl) to execute remote shell scripts. It also communicates with a C2 server to receive commands and uses hardcoded User-Agents ('Wget') to masquerade as legitimate traffic.
